---
const signs = [
  "Teams export data from ERP and run the real workflow in Excel",
  "Follow-ups depend on individual discipline",
  "Managers ask for manual status updates",
  "Exceptions stall because ownership is unclear",
  "Approvals happen in email without a clean audit trail",
  "Reconciliation issues are discovered late",
  "Reports do not match what operators say is happening"
];
---
<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 mb-24 reveal delay-100">
  <div class="bg-surface/50 dark:bg-stone-900/50 rounded-xl p-8 md:p-10 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary dark:text-stone-50 mb-4">Where this fits</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
          Binizam is useful when the system of record exists, but the work still happens manually around it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:col-span-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary dark:text-stone-100 mb-5">Common signs:</p>
        <ul class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {signs.map(sign => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">
              <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber-600 mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0"></div>
              <span>{sign}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
